com.samskivert.util

Interface IntMap<V>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Map<Integer,V>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    HashIntMap

    @ReplacedBy(value="java.util.Map",
            reason="Boxing shouldn\'t be a major concern. It\'s probably better to stick to standard classes rather than worry about a tiny memory or performance gain.")
public interface IntMap<V>
extends Map<Integer,V>
    An int map is a map that uses integers as keys and provides accessors that eliminate the need to create and manipulate superfluous Integer objects. It extends the Map interface and therefore provides all of the standard accessors (for which Integer objects should be supplied as keys).
